value.value: A water soluble, fast-drying paint made of pigment suspended in acrylic polymer emulsion.
A paint that exhibits luminescence, giving off visible light through fluorescence, phosphorescence, or radioluminescence.
A fluid obtained by the distillation of resin harvested from living trees, primarily used as a solvent.

definition.value: Turpentine is composed of terpenes.

value.value: A flammable liquid hydrocarbon mixture produced from natural gas condensates, petroleum distillates, and the distillation of coal tar and peat.

definition.value: Light and heavy varieties may consist of distinct quantities of carbon atoms per molecule.

value.value: Dust which is composed of minerals and trace elements, generated by  finely crushed rock.

definition.value: Rock dust is widely used in mining to prevent coal dust explosions, or in agriculture for organic farming uses.

value.value: Any material containing unstable atoms that emit ionizing radiation as it decays.
An environmental material which is primarily composed of cyanoacrolate.

definition.value: Cyanoacrylates have industrial, medical, and household uses. A strong fast-acting adhesive which is an ester of cyanoacrylic acid.

value.value: A preparation with dye or pigment used to deposit coloration to a substrate.
A stain which has colorants dissolved and/or suspended in a vehicle or solvent, used to add color to wood.

definition.value: Wood stain is designed to add color to substrates, while still leaving some of the substrate visible.
An environmental material which is composed of elastic polymers mixed in a solvent.
Solvents typically used include acetone, hexane, heptane or toluene.
An environmental material which is 1) composed primarily of methyl cellulose and water, and 2) formulated to fix wallpaper to walls.
An environmental material which is 1) manufactured and 2) primarily composed of hydrogen peroxide and ammonia, and 3) when applied to hair, can alter the natural hair pigments for 6-8 weeks.
A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured and 2) composed of alcohol, titanium dioxide, and propylene glycol.
A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured and 2) composed of copper phthalocyanine, iron oxides, water, and biopolymers.
A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured and 2) primarily composed of soybean oil, as well as pigment, resin, and wax.
A colorant fluid which is 1) manufactured, 2) primarily composed of water, as well as glycol, and dye, and 3) intended for use in inkjet printers.
An environmental material which is composed primarily of gases and particles produced by the combustion of petroleum fuels.
A liquid environmental material which 1) contains at least one substance which can act as a chemical colorant.
A function which is realised by a chemical when applied to a material, such that it alters the material's colour.

value.value: Waste which contains toxic components (e.g., heavy metals or radiation) which can cause harm to organisms and/or the environment.
A part of the troposphere which extends from the Earth's surface to 2 km (0 - 6500 ft) height.

A part of the troposphere which extends from 2 km to 4 km (6 500 – 13 000 ft) height in the polar region, from 2 km to 7 km (6 500 – 23 000 ft) height in the temperate region, and from 2 km to 8 km (6 500 – 25 000 ft) height in the tropical region.

A part of the troposphere which extends from 3 km to 8 km (10 000 – 25 000 ft) height in the polar region, from 5 km to 13 km (16 500 – 45 000 ft) height in the temperate region, and from 6 km to 18 km (20 000 – 60 000 ft) height in the tropical region.

definition.value: A part of a cloud.
A cloud part which is closest to the surface of the astronomical body local to the cloud.
A cloud part which is furthest from the surface of the astronomical body local to the cloud.

value.value: A water droplet which exists at temperatures below 0°C (273.15K).
A water ice crystal which is constituted by water molecules aligned in a hexagonal array.
A building part which is maintained such that the number of foreign particulates within it is controlled.

The cleanliness level of a cleanroom is quantified by the number of particles per cubic meter at a predetermined molecule measure.

Cleanrooms are designed to maintain extremely low levels of particulates, such as dust, airborne organisms, or vaporized particles. Cleanroons are used in the manufacture of pharmaceutical items, integrated circuits, CRT, LCD, OLED and microLED displays.
Sediment which contains some chemical contaminant.
Liquid water which is a participant in a water cooling process.
Cooling water is commonly used for cooling automobile internal combustion engines and power stations.
A pipeline network which is used to transport drinking water to consumers.
An industrial building in which water undergoes a purification process to make it fit for human consumption.
A manufactured product which is capable of connecting or disconnecting the conducting path in an electrical circuit, interrupting the electric current or diverting it from one conductor to another.
A waste material which is primarily composed of uneaten food and removed from the food supply chain.
The causes of food waste or loss are numerous and can occur during production, processing, distribution, retail and consumption.
A fluid environmental material which is contained in geologic formations naturally.
A building part which has been constructed to support the provision of intensive care medicine to patients with severe or life-threatening illnesses and injuries.
Liquid water which occurs naturally within the pores of rocks and sediments.
A bioreactor which has a membrane as a part
It is widely used for municipal and industrial wastewater treatment. The membrane is usually used to perform microfiltration, ultrafiltration or osmosis, etc.
A soil horizon which is primarily composed of mineral material.

definition.value: Usually less than 20% organic carbon. The term mineral horizon refers to surface soil/topsoil and subsoil layer of the soil. When user does not/could not refer to the topsoil or subsoil specifically, the broader term, mineral horizon can be used.

value.value: A pipeline network which is used to transport oil to consumers.

An environmental material which consists of either loose sands or partially consolidated sandstone, containing a naturally occurring mixture of sand, clay, and water, soaked with a dense and extremely viscous form of petroleum.
A human construction which is used to transport a material which is primarily composed of liquid or gas through a system of pipes.

definition.value: Pipeline networks typically materials either from 1) a production area to a market area for consumption, 2) a production area to an area for waste disposal.

value.value: A river which has elevated levels of contaminants.

definition.value: The contaminants may cause adverse changes in the ecosystems associated with it.

value.value: Rock which is derived from bedrock through chemical weathering
An environmental material which is composed of insoluble solid particles suspended in a liquid.
A soil horizon which is composed primarily of organic matter.

definition.value: The organic matter is this layer is genreally derived from biomatter.

value.value: Vinasse which is produced during the rectification and distillation of ethanol from sugar cane.
An earth-filled dam which is used for the storage of mining operations byproducts, after separating the ore from the gangue.
A human construction which is used as a storage area for mining tailings.
